The paper discusses deep learning techniques used in face recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the need for larger and more challenging datasets, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and autoencoders in the paper also suggests a potential fit for multimedia (cs.MM) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories.
